GUNMEN suspected to be kidnappers on Tuesday night abducted Kayode Shogbesan, another professor of Fishery at the Moddibo Adama University of Technology (MAUTECH), Yola, Adamawa State. This is the third time in three months that a professor of the university will be abducted. A family source said on Wednesday that Professor Shogbesan, who is also a pastor in the Redeemed Christian Church of God in Yola, was abducted while returning home from work. ALSO READ: Akeredolu calls for divine support to boost developmental projects in Ondo 4 female professors apply for position of Adamawa State… Gunmen attack quarry site in Ekiti, kill night guard PDP sweeps Adamawa LG chairmanship election Adamawa APC rejects LG election results The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Sulaiman Nguroje, confirmed that the don was abducted while returning home from the office between 8:00 p.m and 9:00 p.m on Tuesday. It will be recalled that Professor Felix Ilesanmi of the Department of Urban and Regional Planning of the same university was abducted on November 15. On September 30, Professor Adamu Zata of the Department of Soil Science in the same institution was kidnapped. It was also gathered that on the day Professor Shogbesan was abducted, five members of the same family were kidnapped in Ganye, headquarters of Ganye Local Government Area of the state. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
